nt to know what kind of fire extinguisher to use and how to use it. Section 52 of the Regulation for Construction Projects (213/91) outlines specific locations and circumstances where fire extinguishers must be • Where flammable materials are stored, handled, • Where temporary oil- or gas-fired equipment is being used • Where welding or open-flame cutting is being • On each storey of an enclosed building being constructed or renovated • In workshops, for at least every 300 square metres (3,230 square feet) of floor area. Fire extinguishers must always be • Easily accessible • Well-maintained • Refilled or replaced immediately after use. They must be inspected for defects or deterioration once a month by a competent worker who records the date on the tag.",
